            <entry xml:id="Laf1a9e0ea873446abdecfc63e6471a96" n="340">
               <form>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለንጳስ</foreign>
               <rs type="root"/>
                    </form>
               <sense xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann" xml:id="Dmain"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="not found">n. peregr.</pos> </gramGrp>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">λάμπας</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> lampas </quote>
                        </cit>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ብርሃን፡ ዘለንጳስ፡</foreign> (v. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘለንጰስ፡</foreign>) <ref cRef="Ex." loc="20,18">Ex. 20,18</ref>; M.M. f. 50. </sense>
               
            <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote> lanṗās </quote>
                        </cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>lamp</quote>
                        </cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ብርሃነ፡ ለንጳስ፡ ዐጢቅየ፡</foreign> ʻ<cit type="translation" xml:lang="it">
                            <quote> cinto con la luce della fiammella </quote>
                        </cit>ʼ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2009TawaldaMadehnVittore"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 92 (172) l. 15 (ed.); 93 (173) l. 14 (tr.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl> (ʻL’agiografo usa <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለምጳስ፡</foreign> {the editor gives, perhaps by overcorrection, the form <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለምጳስ፡</foreign> instead of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለንጳስ፡</foreign>} (cf. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:KidaneWaldGeezGramDict"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 569</citedRange>
                        </bibl>), un termine che nella Scrittura è un hapax legomenon. Cf. Es 20, 18. Esso ricorre anche nel Gädl di Eustazio, cf. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Turaev1902Filipos"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page">70</citedRange>
                        </bibl>; <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Turaev1902Filipos"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page">36</citedRange>
                        </bibl>. L’espressione «luce della fiammella» è frequente nel Mäṣḥafa Milād e il Mäṣḥafa Śǝllase, cf. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Wendt1963MiladT"/>
                        </bibl> e <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Wendt1963MiladV"/>
                        </bibl>.ʼ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2009TawaldaMadehnVittore"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 93 (173) n. 45</citedRange>
                        </bibl>) <sense n="L" xml:id="TL"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለንጳስ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                                <quote> lanṗās </quote>
                            </cit>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ልንጳስ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                                <quote> lǝnṗās </quote>
                            </cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                                <quote> lamp </quote>
                            </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                                <quote> torch </quote>
                            </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                                <quote> flame </quote>
                            </cit> <bibl>
                                <ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/>
                                <citedRange unit="page"> 316b</citedRange>
                            </bibl> </sense> <nd/> </sense>
